All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbsBoss
 
AbsBullet
The AbsBullet class is an abstract representation of a bullet entity in a game.
AbsCreature
An AbsCreature is an AbsEntity with health and the ability to die.
AbsEnemy
An AbsEnemy is an abstract class that contains all the methods and variables for an AbsCreature to be an enemy.
AbsEnemyBullet
An AbsEnemyBullet is an abstract class that represents an enemy bullet.
AbsEntity
An AbsEntity is an abstract class that represents an object that can be visualized and moved on the playing field.
AbsFactory
The AbsFactory class is an abstract class that serves as a factory for creating various game objects.
AbsInput
An AbsInput class is an abstract class that contains all the necessary information for the game logic to work.
AbsPlayer
The AbsPlayer class is an abstract class representing a player in the game.
AbsPlayerBullet
An AbsPlayerBullet is an AbsBullet shot by an AbsPlayer.
AbsPowerUp
An AbsPowerUp is an abstract class that represents a power-up object in the game.
AbsScoreBoard
An AbsScoreBoard is an abstract class that represents a scoreboard in the game.
AbsVisualManager
An AbsVisualManager is an abstract class that represents a visual manager in the game.
Game
The main game class controls the game logic and elements.
J2DActionListener
The J2DActionListener class implements the ActionListener interface to handle button actions in a Java2D-based visualization.

MovementComponent
The MovementComponent class represents the movement component of an object in a 2D space.

The MovementSystem class handles the updating of MovementComponents for various entities in the game.
